Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the broiler or grill to high. If you do not
have either, preheat the oven to 500 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water
to a boil. Soak the @wooden skewers{4} in a shallow #dish{} of water. Core, seed,
and dice the @roma tomato{1}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Zest, then
halve the @lemon{1}. Finely chop the @basil{1/2%ounce}(finely chopped). Add the
@orzo pasta{6%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for ~{6-8%minutes}, until
al dente. Drain.

Marinate the tomatoes: Place the tomatoes and @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}
in a small #bowl{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss, then
set aside to marinate.

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} in a small #pot{} over medium heat. Once melted,
remove from the heat and stir in half the basil and a squeeze of lemon juice.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drain the tomatoes. Halve, pit, and cube the @avocado{1/2}. Once the orzo is
ready, toss it into a large #bowl{} with the tomatoes, half the avocado, the
remaining basil, a large drizzle of @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon}, and a squeeze
of lemon juice (to taste). Season with salt and pepper.

> Eat the remaining avocado with your eggs in the morning!

Toss the @shrimp{10%ounce} in a medium bowl with a drizzle of olive oil, the
lemon zest, garlic, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Thread them onto the skewers
and either broil on a #baking sheet{} or grill for ~{3-4%minutes}, flipping once,
until cooked through.

Plate: Serve the shrimp skewers on a bed of orzo & avocado salad. Drizzle with
the lemon-basil butter and enjoy!